snippet.textDisplay: So let me get this straight. You start from frozen Stonehenge in Scotland and fly with a flying saucer to a beach of southern france, from there with a boat through the mediterranean sea fighting a kraken on the way to egypt. Walking through the desert with a man who became a dungeon, crossing a river with a submarine and going through a swamp full of darkness, fighting a pile of puke, arriving at a village full of shy little green creatures, jumping down a hole to a maze with an illuminating neon board all the way deeper into a jungle in the middle of the earth which is full of dinosaurs and next to hell where the revived spirit of a dead alien resides who was brought up by human stepparents who were right your next door american neighbours? Seems legit. And that's only the second half of Earthbound!

Trust me.
